# HerCare App Implementation Plan (Phase 5)

Phase 5 will transform the application from a visual prototype into a fully functional local web app. We will implement **Local Data Persistence** so that user data is saved locally on their device, surviving page refreshes or app closing/reopening.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. `useLocalStorage` Hook (`src/hooks/useLocalStorage.ts`)
We will create a custom React Hook that transparently reads and writes state to the browser's `localStorage` API. This pattern allows us to persist data without setting up a complex external database yet.

### 2. State Persistence Integration
We will replace standard `useState` hooks with our new `useLocalStorage` hook across several core components:
- **`App.tsx`**: Persist `appState`. Instead of starting at the Splash screen every single time, the app will remember if the user has already completed the setup wizard, skipping straight to the Home Dashboard on subsequent visits.
- **`SetupWizard.tsx` & `Home.tsx`**: Save the user's customized Name/Nickname and Shift Preferences to local storage, and retrieve them on the Home Dashboard header ("Hi, [Name]! 👋").
- **`Wellness.tsx`**: Persist the number of water glasses logged and the saved mood, so a refresh doesn't zero out her progress.
- **`Meals.tsx`**: Persist the toggle states of logged meals.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> This phase implements local data saving, meaning the app will now truly "remember" user states! Do you approve of this approach for Phase 5?
> 
> *Note: Since this relies on `localStorage`, data will be saved accurately per device/browser. If the app is later packaged as a mobile app (e.g., via Capacitor or React Native), this safely translates into persistent mobile storage.*

## Verification Plan
1. Create the hook and integrate it components. 
2. Start the app. Pass the setup screen. Refresh the page. Test that the app skips the setup explicitly and retains the Home dashboard state.
3. Log water/mood, refresh the page, and ensure the state is fully preserved.
